Key Arguments: The proposed Bill is an insult to free political speech and should be abandoned.
The real threat to democracy comes from censorship by foreign tech giants like Facebook and YouTube.
These platforms have interfered in democracy by censoring parliamentary proceedings and election candidates.
Social media platforms should be treated as common carriers, not publishers.
Main Themes: Role of tech giants in democracy
Comparison of social media platforms to common carriers
Notable Quotes: There was no time in history where the people censoring free speech were the good guys – RFK Jr
If it is lawful to say something on a soap box in the town square, it’s unlawful for a social media platform to censor it.
